This paper discusses the use of message brokers for distributed communication, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also explores the performance of different protocols, which could be considered a topic in Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses fault tolerance and high availability, which are topics in Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Distributed Systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the features and performance of specific protocols, which could be considered a topic in Systems and Control (cs.SY).
